
###Block: Feats
Breath Weapon Exemplar	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.31	DESC:Your breath weapon's damage continues to improve despite your dabbling in paragonhood.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Breath weapon racial trait; Draconic Exemplar or dragon exemplar class feature, dragon character.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Breath Weapon	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Draconic Exemplar],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Paragon ~ Dragon Exemplar]	PRERACE:1,Dragon	BENEFIT:Increase the damage dealt by your breath weapon by 1d6. In addition, you further increase the damage dealt by your breath weapon by 2d6 for every other dragon feat you possess, up to a maximum of 1d6 points of damage per character level, or 20d6 at 20th level. Normal: Your breath weapon deals 1d6 points of damage.	BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponDice|min(1+((count("ABILITIES","CATEGORY=FEAT","TYPE=Dragon)-1)*2),TL)
Cloud Walk	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.31	DESC:You are able to tread across clouds as easily as stone.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character (silver sept) or dragon companion (silver sept).	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Silver	BENEFIT:You can air walk (as the spell) on clouds, fog, and mist. This ability is a constant supernatural effect.
Corrupt Water	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.31	DESC:You can stagnate water into a foul, unusable liquid.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Heritage (black sept) class feature or Draconic Heritage (black sept), 3 HD.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Black	PRELEVEL:MIN=3	BENEFIT:You can cast putrefy food and drinkapg as a spell-like ability at will. In addition, you can spoil up to 10 cubic feet of still water within a 10-foot burst as a standard action. Liquid- based magic items (such as potions) and items in a creature's possession must succeed on a Will save (DC 10 + 1/2 your dragon paragon level + your Charisma modifier) or be ruined. You can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 3 + your Charisma modifier.
Crush	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.31	DESC:You can crush foes with your body mass.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon exemplar (large) class feature or Greater Draconic Exemplar.	PREVARGTEQ:DragonSizeTracker,4	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Dragon Exemplar],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Greater Draconic Exemplar]	BENEFIT:While flying or jumping, you can crush foes by landing on them as a standard action, affecting as many creatures as fit in your space. Creatures in this area are pinned unless they succeed on a Reflex saving throw (DC equals 10 + 1/2 your Hit Dice + your Constitution modifier). Pinned creatures take 2d6 points + 1-1/2 times your Strength bonus during your next round unless you move off of them. If you choose to maintain the pin, you must succeed on a combat maneuver check to do so as normal. Pinned creatures take damage from the crush each round if they don't escape. This attack is only effective against creatures three or more size categories smaller than you.
