Deific Spellcasting	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.31	DESC:You are able to use your arcane talents to channel divine gifts.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon exemplar class feature, ability to cast arcane spells, dragon companion (gold, silver, or umbral sept).	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Silver,Dragon Sept ~ Gold,Dragon Sept ~ Umbral	PREMULT:1,[PRECLASS:1,Draconic Companion=1],[PRERACE:1,Dragon]	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Paragon ~ Dragon Exemplar	PRESPELLTYPE:1,Arcane=1	BENEFIT:You can utilize divine magic using your arcane spellcasting. Add all spells on the cleric spell list of 4th level and lower to the dragon paragon spell list as arcane spells of the same level.
Draconic Companion	TYPE:General	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.31	DESC:You have forged a powerful bond with a true dragon that now serves as your companion.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Knowledge (arcana) 4 ranks; animal companion, divine bond (mount), mount, or nature bond (animal companion) class feature with an effective druid level of 4th; ability to speak Draconic.	PRELANG:1,Draconic	PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (arcana)=4	BENEFIT:You can select a draconic companion from the list of draconic companions to serve as your animal companion or special mount. You acquire and advance this creature in the same way as the mount or animal companion detailed in the class feature used as a prerequisite for this feat. You can also dismiss the creature as dictated by your class feature. You must meet additional prerequisites to choose a draconic companion, as noted in the companion's description. Special: At the GM's decision, other abilities that grant an animal companion or special mount can meet the prerequisites of this feat, but only if the character's effective druid level is 4th or higher.	PRELEVEL:MIN=4	DEFINE:DraconicCompanionLVL|0	DEFINE:Pool_DraconicCompanion|0	BONUS:VAR|Pool_DraconicCompanion|1
Draconic Companion Mastery	TYPE:General	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.31	DESC:Your draconic companion's abilities improve to that of a much older dragon.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Draconic Companion, Knowledge (arcana) 7 ranks; animal companion, divine bond (mount), mount, or nature bond (animal companion) class feature with an effective druid level of 4th; ability to speak Draconic.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Draconic Companion	PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Arcana)=7	BENEFIT:Your draconic companion gains the mastery advancement detailed in its stat block. Normal: A draconic companion cannot obtain its mastery advancement regardless of your effective druid level.	DEFINE:CompanionAdvancement|0	BONUS:VAR|CompanionAdvancement|1
Draconic Exemplar	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:You grow much larger than your age would normally allow.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character, base attack bonus +5.	PRERACE:1,Dragon	PRETOTALAB:5	BENEFIT:You size permanently increases to Medium, granting you a +2 size bonus to Strength as well as the usual size qualities for Medium creatures. Normal: Dragon characters are Small creatures.	BONUS:VAR|DragonSize|1
Draconic Heritage	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:You manifest your draconic heritage in the form of fantastic powers that correlate to your sept.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: No levels in a class that has the heritage class feature; Cha 13; Eldritch Heritage (draconic), dragon character, dragon companion, or kobold;3 Hit Dice.	PREMULT:1,[PRECLASS:1,Draconic Companion=1],[PRERACE:1,Dragon,Kobold]	!PRECLASS:1,Dragon Paragon=1	PRESTAT:1,CHA=13	BENEFIT:Select one dragon paragon heritage. If you have the dragon type, your heritage must match your sept. You gain the first-level heritage power for the selected heritage. For purposes of using that power, treat your dragon paragon level as equal to your character level -2. You do not gain any of the other heritage abilities. Special: If you gain levels in a class that grants the heritage class feature, you can immediately trade this feat for Heritage Focus or a dragon feat of your choice. You must meet the chosen feat's prerequisites, if any.	BONUS:VAR|Pool_Dragon_Paragon_Heritage_Level_One|1	DEFINE:Pool_Dragon_Paragon_Heritage_Level_One|0
Draconic Spell Resistance	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:You are able to shrug off spells due to your magical nature.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character or dragon companion.	PRERACE:1,Dragon	BENEFIT:You gain spell resistance equal to 6 + your character levels.	SR:6+TL
Expanded Camouflage	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:You can hide easily in a wider variety of terrains.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character (green sept) or dragon companion (green sept), camouflage racial trait.	PREMULT:1,[PRECLASS:1,Draconic Companion=1],[PRERACE:1,Dragon]	PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Green,Green Dragon Sept ~ Camouflage	BENEFIT:Select two terrains from the ranger's list of favored terrains from the following list: cold, desert, mountain, plains, planes (any except Material Plane), swamp, underground, urban, or water. You gain a +4 racial bonus on Stealth checks made to hide in the selected terrain.	CHOOSE:STRING|cold|desert|mountain|plains|planes|swamp|underground|urban|water	SELECT:2	MULT:YES	STACK:NO
Extra Breath Attack	TYPE:General	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:You can use your breath weapon more often than others.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Breath weapon racial trait.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Breath Weapon	BENEFIT:You can use your breath weapon two additional times each day. After using your breath weapon, you must wait 1d4 rounds before using it again. Special: You can select this feat multiple times. Normal: You can use your breath weapon once per day.	BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponTimes|2	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE
Extended Heritage Power	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:You can call upon your heritage for longer periods of time.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cha 13, heritage class feature.	PRESTAT:1,CHA=13	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Heritage	BENEFIT:Select one heritage power that measures its of uses per day in feet, rounds, minutes, or hours. Add your Charisma bonus to the number of feet, rounds, minutes, or hours per day that you can use the selected ability.
