Extra Heritage Power	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:You can use your heritage powers more often than most.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cha 13, heritage class feature.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Heritage	PRESTAT:1,CHA=13	BENEFIT:Select one heritage power that you possess with a number of limited uses per day. You can use the selected heritage power two additional times per day. If the selected ability measures its uses per day in feet, rounds, minutes, or hours, add 2 to the number of feet, rounds, minutes, or hours per day that you can use the selected ability. Special: You can select this feat multiple times. Its effects don't stack. Each time you select this feat, apply its benefits to a different heritage power that you possess.
Fast Burrow	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:You can dig through the earth with tremendous speed.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character or dragon companion, 20-ft. burrow speed.	PREMOVE:1,Burrow=20	PREMULT:1,[PRECLASS:1,Draconic Companion=1],[PRERACE:1,Dragon]	BENEFIT:Your burrow speed increases by 10 feet.	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Burrow|10
Fast Flyer	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:Your flying speed drastically improves.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon companion, Fly 8 ranks.	PRESKILL:1,Fly=8	PRECLASS:1,Draconic Companion=1	BENEFIT:Your fly speed increases by 20 feet. Special: You can select this feat up to three times.	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Fly|20	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|Feat_FastFlyTaken|1	DEFINE:Feat_FastFlyTaken|0	PREVARLT:Feat_FastFlyTaken,3
Fast Swimmer	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:You are able to swim impossibly fast.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Heritage (sea sept) class feature or Draconic Heritage (sea sept), sea strider heritage power.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Sea	BENEFIT:Your swim speed increases by 10 feet. Special: You can select this feat up to five times.	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Swim|10	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|Feat_FastSwimmerTaken|1	DEFINE:Feat_FastSwimmerTaken|0	PREVARLT:Feat_FastSwimmerTaken,5
Freezing Fog	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.32	DESC:You can manifest your breath weapon in the form of a biting, frozen fog.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Heritage (white sept) class feature or Draconic Heritage (white sept), breath weapon racial trait, 13 HD.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ White	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Breath Weapon	PRELEVEL:MIN=13	BENEFIT:When you use your breath weapon, you can choose to breath an icy cloud of fog instead of dealing damage. This fog functions as solid fog. Each round on your turn, starting when you breathe the cloud, the fog deals 2d6 points of cold damage to each creature and object within it. Additionally, any surface that the cloud touches becomes coated in icy rime, creating the effects of a grease spell. A creature with the icewalking racial trait or the snow acclimation heritage power is not affected by this grease effect.
Extra Natural Weapons	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.33	DESC:You possess the ability to strike foes with additional weapons located upon your body.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Base attack bonus +11, dragon character.	PRERACE:1,Dragon	PRETOTALAB:11	BENEFIT:You gain one additional natural weapon. If you belong to an imperial dragon sept, you gain a gore attack. This attack is a secondary natural weapon that deals 1d8 points of damage (or 1d6 points if Medium). If you belong to any non-imperial dragon sept, you gain two wing attacks. This attack is a secondary natural weapon that deals 1d6 points of damage (or 1d4 points if Medium).	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Wing|PREVAREQ:HasWings,0	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Gore|PREVARGTEQ:HasWings,1
Greater Draconic Exemplar	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.33	DESC:Your body grows to a tremendous size.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Draconic Exemplar, Dragon character, base attack bonus +13.	PRERACE:1,Dragon	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Draconic Exemplar	PRETOTALAB:13	BENEFIT:You size permanently increases to Large, granting you a +4 size bonus to Strength, a +2 size bonus to Constitution, and a -2 penalty to Dexterity as well as the usual size qualities for Medium creatures.	BONUS:VAR|DragonSize|1
Greater Draconic Heritage	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.33	DESC:The power of your draconic heritage continues to grow.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: No levels in a class that has the heritage class feature; Cha 17; Draconic Heritage; Improved Draconic Heritage; Eldritch Heritage (draconic), dragon character, dragon companion, or kobold; 17 HD.	PRESTAT:1,CHA=17	BENEFIT:You gain a 15th-level power (or lower) dragon paragon heritage power from the heritage that you selected with the Draconic Heritage feat. For purposes of using that power, treat your dragon paragon level as your dragon paragon level for all your dragon paragon heritage powers granted by this feat, Draconic Heritage, and Improved Draconic Heritage. Special: If you gain levels in a class that grants the heritage class feature, you can immediately trade this feat for a dragon feat of your choice. You must meet the chosen feat's prerequisites, if any.
Greater Ice Walking	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.33	DESC:You are able to scale icy surfaces with ease.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Ice walking heritage power.	BENEFIT:You can climb icy surfaces with ease. In effect, you are treated as constantly being under a nonmagical version of the spider climb spell, save you cannot cling to surfaces that are not covered with ice or snow. If you possess a climb speed, this feat doubles the normal +8 racial bonus to Climb checks normally afforded to creatures with a climb speed while climbing across icy surfaces.
Groundling	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.33	DESC:You are able to sense subtle vibrations in the earth, alerting you to nearby movement.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character (crystal or forest sept) or dragon companion (crystal or forest sept), blindsense 20 ft..	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Crystal,Dragon Sept ~ Forest	BENEFIT:You gain tremorsense to a distance equal to half your blindsense.	BONUS:VAR|TremorsenseRange|BlindsenseRange/2
Heritage Focus	TYPE:General	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.33	DESC:Your heritage powers outstrip your dabbling in paragonhood.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Heritage class feature, base attack bonus +5.	PRETOTALAB:5	BENEFIT:If you are a multiclass paragon, any heritage powers you possess are calculated as though your dragon paragon level were four higher, to a maximum level equal to your character level. If this feat brings your effective dragon paragon level high enough for you to obtain a new heritage power, you gain that power. Special: This feat has no effect if you are not a multiclass dragon paragon.
Ice Glide	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.33	DESC:You can burrow through ice and snow at tremendous speeds.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character (white sept) or dragon companion (white sept), 3 HD.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ White	BENEFIT:You gain a burrow speed of 20 feet.	MOVE:Burrow,20
Improved Camouflage	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.33	DESC:You are able to disappear from sight while in certain terrains.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Stealth 13 ranks, dragon character (green sept) or dragon companion (green sept), camouflage racial trait.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Green	BENEFIT:Select forest, jungle, or one terrain that you have selected with the Expanded Camouflage feat. You are a master at hiding in that terrain, and while within the chosen terrain, you can use the Stealth skill to hide, even while being observed. Special: You can select this feat multiple times. Its effects don't stack. Each time you select this feat, choose a different terrain to apply its benefits to.
Improved Draconic Spell Resistance	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.33	DESC:Your resistance to spells strengthens.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Draconic Spell Resistance, dragon character or dragon companion, character level 11th.	BENEFIT:Your spell resistance improves to 11 + your character level.	SR:11+TL
Improved Draconic Heritage	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.33	DESC:The power of your draconic heritage continues to grow.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: No levels in a class that has the heritage class feature; Cha 15; Draconic Heritage; Eldritch Heritage (draconic), dragon character, dragon companion, or kobold; 11 HD.	BENEFIT:You gain either the 3rd-level or the 9th-level power (your choice) of the heritage you selected with the Draconic Heritage feat. For purposes of using that power, treat your dragon paragon level as equal to your character level -2. You do not gain any of the other heritage abilities. Special: You may select this feat multiple times. Each time you select the feat, it applies to a different bloodline power for that bloodline available at dragon paragon level 3 or 9. If you gain levels in a class that grants the heritage class feature, you can immediately trade this feat for a dragon feat of your choice. You must meet the chosen feat's prerequisites, if any.
Improved Manipulate Flames	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.34	DESC:You can command fire magic even after using your manipulate flames ability.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Draconic Spell Resistance, manipulate flames heritage power, arcane caster level 13th.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Draconic Spell Resistance	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Red Dragon Paragon Heritage ~ Manipulate Flames	BENEFIT:After using your manipulate flames heritage power, for 1 round you can control the next fire spell to be cast within 20 feet of you, allowing you to make all decisions normally allowed to the caster. This includes the spell's targets, affected area, and so on. You may even cancel the spell if desired.
Incinerating Breath	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.34	DESC:You can reduce enemies to ashen slag with your blazing breath.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character (red sept) or dragon companion (red sept), breath weapon racial trait, character level 15th.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Red	BENEFIT:Whenever you reduce a creature to 0 or fewer hit points with your breath weapon, the creature is immediately slain and reduced to ash unless it succeeds on a Fortitude save (DC 10 + 1/2 your dragon paragon level + your Charisma modifier). Creatures destroyed in this way can only be restored to life through true resurrection or similar magic.
Lunging Bite	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.34	DESC:You can strike foes at a great distance with your bite attack.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Weapon Focus (bite), base attack bonus +6.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Weapon Focus (Bite)	PRETOTALAB:6	BENEFIT:Increase the reach of your bite attack by 5 feet. This feat stacks with other effects that improve reach, such as the Lunge feat.	BONUS:WEAPONPROF=Bite|REACH|5
Mirage	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.34	DESC:You can make yourself appear to be in two places at once.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Electricity aura heritage power, heritage (blue sept) class feature or Draconic Heritage (blue sept), 11 HD.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Blue	PRELEVEL:MIN=11	BENEFIT:You can spend 1 round of your electricity aura as a swift action in order to appear to be in two places at once, as project image. Additionally, you can use the illusion as the point of origin for attacks made with your breath weapon.
Obliterating Bite	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.34	DESC:Your bite attack channels negative energy with such destructive force that it disintegrates foes.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Obliterate heritage power, dragon character (void sept) or dragon companion (void sept); character level 9th.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Void	BENEFIT:When you reduce a creature to 0 or fewer hit points with your bite attack, the creature must succeed on a Fortitude save or be immediately slain and reduced to ashes, as the disintegrate spell. The save DC is equal to 10 + 1/2 your character level + your Charisma modifier.
Powerful Breath	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.35	DESC:Your breath weapon is intense enough to damage even the most prepared combatants.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon companion or dragon character, breath weapon racial trait.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Breath Weapon	PRERACE:1,Dragon	BENEFIT:A creature that succeeds on its saving throw against your breath weapon takes half damage from the attack. Normal: Creatures that succeed on their saving throw against your breath weapon take no damage.
Powerful Bite	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.35	DESC:Your bite attack benefits greatly from your physical strength.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Weapon Focus (bite), dragon character or dragon companion.	PRERACE:1,Dragon	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Weapon Focus (Bite)	BENEFIT:Your bite attack always deals its indicated damage plus 1-1/2 times your Strength bonus, even if you have more than one attack per round.
Quick Breath Weapon	TYPE:General	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.35	DESC:You can unleash your breath weapon and deliver an attack before your opponent is the wiser.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Ability Focus (breath weapon), breath weapon racial trait, base attack bonus +6.	BENEFIT:On your turn, you can use your breath weapon in place of one of your melee attacks. You must choose the melee attack with the highest base attack bonus to use your breath weapon. Normal: Using a breath weapon is a standard action.
Reptile Whisperer	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.35	DESC:You speak the language of serpents and commune with them at will.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Draconic Heritage (black), dragon character (black sept), or dragon companion (black sept); ability to cast speak with animals.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Black	BENEFIT:You gain a constant speak with animals effect as a spell-like ability, but only to speak with reptilian creatures. If you are a dragon paragon, you can use your speak with animals heritage spell to speak with any animals, not just reptilian animals.
Surprise Breath	TYPE:General	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.35	DESC:Your breath weapon is especially devastating when you catch your foes off-guard.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Breath Weapon Focus, breath weapon racial trait, sneak attack +5d6, base attack bonus +10.	BENEFIT:You can add your sneak attack damage to your breath weapon if the targets are flat-footed. This additional damage only applies to your breath weapon if it is used to deal hit point damage, and the additional damage is of the same type as your breath weapon. If a target succeeds on its saving throw to negate or halve the damage, it also negates or halves the sneak attack damage.
Starflight	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.35	DESC:You can soar throughout the skies with little difficulty.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character (any outer dragon sept) or dragon companion (any outer dragon sept); no breath racial trait.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Dragon Sept Outer	BENEFIT:In outer space, you can survive in the void and fly at incredible speeds. Travel times vary, but a trip within a single solar system should take 3d20 hours and a trip beyond should take 3d20 days or more if you know the way to your destination. If you are capable of carrying riders while flying, you can carry one rider of one size category smaller than yourself, four passengers two sizes smaller, eight passengers three sizes smaller, or 16 passengers four or more sizes smaller. Passengers are protected from the void of outer space.
Steeled Scales	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.35	DESC:Your scales are tougher than steel and impervious to magic.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character or dragon companion, forest sept, DR/magic class feature, dragon paragon level 7th.	PRECLASS:1,Dragon Paragon=7	PRERACE:1,Dragon	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Forest	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Damage Reduction Magic	BENEFIT:Your damage reduction changes from DR/magic to DR/adamantine.	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Damage Reduction ~ Adamantine	BONUS:VAR|DamageReduction_Adamantine|ParagonDragonDR	BONUS:VAR|DragonParagonDamageReductionMagic|1
Stony Death	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.35	DESC:Your breath transforms its victims into stone statues.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character (forest sept) or dragon companion (forest sept), breath weapon racial trait, character level 17th.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Forest	PRELEVEL:MIN=17	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Breath Weapon	BENEFIT:Whenever you reduce a creature to 0 or fewer hit points with your breath weapon, the creature is immediately petrified, as flesh to stone, unless it succeeds on a Fortitude save (DC 10 + 1/2 your dragon paragon level + your Charisma modifier). This ability is a death effect.
Trackless Presence	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.35	DESC:If you are impossible to track if you don't wish to be found.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Woodland stride heritage power.	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Woodland Stride Heritage	BENEFIT:You leave no trail in natural surroundings and cannot be tracked. You may wish to leave a trail if so desired.
True Courage	TYPE:Dragon	CATEGORY:FEAT	SOURCEPAGE:p.35	DESC:You continue fighting long after others would have faltered.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Diehard, Endurance, 17 HD, dragon character (silver sept).	PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Diehard,Endurance	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Silver	PRELEVEL:MIN=17	BENEFIT:While you are at 0 or fewer hit points, you do not lose 1 hit point when you take an action (though you are still staggered). If you take damage or are the target of a spell that causes your death, you remain alive for 1 round and can act normally (you are not staggered for this final round).
